## Part 1: Performance Testing (2-3 hours)

### Test Scenarios

**Test 1.1: 100 Tasks Render Time**
```typescript
// Generate 100 test tasks
const generateTestTasks = (count: number) => {
  return Array.from({ length: count }, (_, i) => ({
    id: `test-${i}`,
    title: `Task ${i + 1}`,
    description: `Description for task ${i + 1}`,
    status: ['backlog', 'todo', 'in-progress', 'review', 'done'][i % 5],
    priority: ['low', 'medium', 'high'][i % 3],
    tags: [`tag-${i % 5}`],
    subtasks: i % 3 === 0 ? [
      { id: `st-${i}-1`, title: 'Subtask 1', completed: i % 2 === 0, priority: 'medium' }
    ] : [],
    createdAt: new Date().toISOString(),
  }));
};
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Board view: < 1s initial render
- List view: < 1s initial render
- Switching views: < 500ms
- Sorting in list view: < 300ms
- Filtering: < 200ms

**Test 1.2: 500 Tasks Stress Test**
- Generate 500 tasks
- Measure render time (should be < 3s)
- Scroll performance (60fps)
- Memory usage (< 100MB increase)

**Test 1.3: Bulk Actions Performance**
- Select 50 tasks
- Change status: < 500ms
- Delete: < 500ms with undo

### Optimization Strategies (If Needed)

**Strategy 1: Virtualization**
```typescript
// Use react-window for large lists
import { FixedSizeList } from 'react-window';

<FixedSizeList
  height={600}
  itemCount={sortedTasks.length}
  itemSize={80}
  width="100%"
>
  {({ index, style }) => (
    <div style={style}>
      <TaskRow task={sortedTasks[index]} />
    </div>
  )}
</FixedSizeList>
```

**Strategy 2: Memoization**
```typescript
// Memoize expensive computations
const sortedTasks = useMemo(() => {
  // Sorting logic
}, [tasks, sortColumn, sortDirection]);

const TaskRow = React.memo(({ task }) => {
  // Row rendering
}, (prev, next) => prev.task.id === next.task.id);
```

**Strategy 3: Debouncing**
```typescript
