## Part 2: Accessibility Audit (2-3 hours)

### Test Scenarios

**Test 2.1: Keyboard Navigation**

**Board View:**
- [ ] Tab through columns (focus visible)
- [ ] Tab through cards (focus visible)
- [ ] Enter on card → opens detail panel
- [ ] Esc in detail panel → closes panel
- [ ] Arrow keys navigate cards (optional enhancement)

**List View:**
- [ ] Tab through table rows
- [ ] Space on checkbox → select row
- [ ] Enter on row → opens detail panel
- [ ] Shift+Click → bulk select range
- [ ] Ctrl/Cmd+A → select all

**Detail Panel:**
- [ ] Tab cycles through fields
- [ ] Tab traps focus (can't tab outside)
- [ ] Esc closes panel
- [ ] All inputs accessible via keyboard

**Test 2.2: Screen Reader**

**Tools:**
- macOS: VoiceOver (Cmd+F5)
- Windows: NVDA (free, nvaccess.org)

**Check:**
- [ ] All buttons have labels
- [ ] All inputs have labels
- [ ] Status changes announced ("Task moved to In Progress")
- [ ] Error messages announced
- [ ] Loading states announced
- [ ] Card details announced (title, status, priority)

**Test 2.3: ARIA Labels**

**Required:**
```typescript
// Column headers
<button aria-label="Sort by title">Title</button>

// Bulk actions
<button aria-label="Change status for selected tasks">Change Status</button>

// Card actions
<button aria-label={`Edit ${task.title}`}>✏️</button>
<button aria-label={`Delete ${task.title}`}>🗑️</button>

// Loading states
<div role="status" aria-live="polite">Loading tasks...</div>
```

**Test 2.4: Color Contrast (WCAG AA: 4.5:1)**

**Check:**
- [ ] Text on backgrounds (light mode)
- [ ] Text on backgrounds (dark mode)
- [ ] Priority badges (red, yellow, blue)
- [ ] Status labels
- [ ] Disabled states

**Tool:** WebAIM Contrast Checker (webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/)

### Fixes Required

**If contrast fails:**
```typescript
