## Part 3: Responsive Design (2 hours)

### Test Scenarios

**Test 3.1: Breakpoints**

**Mobile (320px-767px):**
- [ ] Board view: Horizontal scroll (columns side-by-side)
- [ ] List view: Hide less critical columns (tags, progress)
- [ ] Bulk actions: Vertical stack (buttons wrap)
- [ ] Detail panel: Full screen modal
- [ ] Touch targets: 48x48px minimum

**Tablet (768px-1023px):**
- [ ] Board view: Show 2-3 columns
- [ ] List view: Show most columns
- [ ] Bulk actions: Horizontal layout
- [ ] Detail panel: Modal (600px max width)

**Desktop (1024px+):**
- [ ] Board view: Show all columns
- [ ] List view: Show all columns
- [ ] Detail panel: Side panel or modal

**Test 3.2: Touch Gestures**

- [ ] Swipe to dismiss detail panel (mobile)
- [ ] Pull to refresh (optional)
- [ ] Long press for context menu (optional)

**Test 3.3: Mobile Safari Issues**

**Common issues:**
- 100vh includes URL bar (use viewport units workaround)
- Touch delay (use touch-action: manipulation)
- Zoom on input focus (use font-size: 16px+)

**Fixes:**
```css
/* Viewport height fix */
.detail-panel {
  height: 100dvh; /* Dynamic viewport height */
}

/* Touch optimization */
button {
  touch-action: manipulation;
  -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;
}

/* Prevent zoom on focus */
input, textarea, select {
  font-size: 16px; /* Minimum to prevent zoom */
}
```

